</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Adam Neumann and capital providers including D=
an Loeb=E2=80=99s Third Point are exploring an offer to buy WeWork Inc. out=
 of bankruptcy, according to a letter sent to WeWork=E2=80=99s lawyers that=
 was seen by Bloomberg News.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Neumann and Third Point have been trying to ge=
t information from WeWork necessary to formulate a bid since December, acco=
rding to the letter. More recently they=E2=80=99ve worked to put together a=
 bankruptcy financing package for the co-working firm.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The bid would be for the entire company or its=
 assets, according to the letter. It did not include details of how much Ne=
umann, who co-founded WeWork, stood ready to offer for the firm.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Currently, WeWork=E2=80=99s bankruptcy plan pr=
oposes handing ownership to the company=E2=80=99s most senior debt holders,=
 including those holding its credit line, first-lien notes and second-lien =
notes, according to court papers. Third-lien noteholders and unsecured cred=
itors are likely to be wiped out.</p>
</blockquote>
