sortium =E2=80=9Cled by members of the senior management team of our Russia=
n businesses, and supported by four financial investors,=E2=80=9D none of w=
hom are currently subject to sanctions.=C2=A0=E2=80=9CThe cash consideratio=
n will be paid in Chinese Yuan (CNH) outside of Russia,=E2=80=9D though it =
is denominated in rubles (=E2=80=9Ca cash equivalent of at least RUB 230 bi=
llion=E2=80=9D). The stock consists of up to 176 million Yandex shares that=
 the buyers already own or plan to acquire in Russia, a bit more than half =
of Yandex=E2=80=99s 325 million outstanding shares. So Yandex will:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Get rid of 95% of its assets,</li>=09=
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Cancel a bit more than half of its shares=
, and</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Get about $2.6 billion in ca=
sh.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Shrinking your business by 95%, and your share=
 count by 54%, leaves you with, uh, too many shares? Or rather, each share =
is worth a lot less?=C2=A0Yandex plans to use some of the cash =E2=80=9Cto =
finance the development of the retained international businesses,=E2=80=9D =
and use the rest on a stock buyback, to further shrink its capitalization t=
o match its shrinking business.</p>
